  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "note_47",
      "text": "Computes every pairwise correlation among the wired columns and reports them one row per pair: var_i, var_j, r, p-value and n. Choose Pearson (linear) or Spearman (rank / monotonic), or leave it on Auto — which uses Spearman if any column fails a Jarque-Bera normality check, so the whole matrix stays on one comparable method. Uses pairwise-complete rows (a missing value drops only that pair-row), and warns on small samples and, for Spearman, on ties. Quick-plot draws the correlation heatmap.",
